data.name: QRGeneratorTabPage.HelpString
data.value:
This tool was raised for create QR codes based in a file with extension txt only. The file must have this format on all your lines: ICCID +White space+ LPA. Follow the example below.
11111111111111111111 LPA:A2A2A2A2A2A2A2A2A2A2A2A2A2A2A2AA2A2A2A2A2A2A2A22A2AA2AA2A2A2A2A2A2.
Both them need be separated by one white space and, the iccid and lpa must be on the same line, being that the ICCID need be the first, and the LPA the last, i.e. the white space is in the middle of the two.
GDBR - Created in: 01/30/2023 by (tsemh)Tiago B. Silva - Intern

data.name: PNNTextBox.HelpString
data.value:
EF PNN (PLMN Network Name) - 17 Bytes:
Bytes | Description | M/O 1 | Network Full Name IEI (0x43) | M 2 | Length of Network Full Name contents | M 3 | Coding Scheme and Spare Bits in the last Byte (0x8X) | M 4 to 17 | Network Full Name - Packed 7-bit | M Unused bytes are set to 0xFF.
Encoding: SMS Default 7-bit Alphabet
Based On: ETSI TS 131.102 ETSI TS 24.008 ETSI TS 23.038

data.name: SPNTextBox.HelpString
data.value:
EF SPN (Service Provider Name) - 17 Bytes:
Bytes | Description | M/O 1 | Display Condition (0x00, 0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04 or 0xFF) | M 2 to 17 | Service Provider Name | M Unused bytes are set to 0xFF.
Encoding: SMS Default 7-bit Alphabet
Based On: ETSI TS 131.102

data.name: MenuTitleTextBox.HelpString
data.value:
EF Menu Title - 19 Bytes:
Bytes | Description | M / O 1 | RFU(0x00) | M 2 | RFU(0x00) | M 3 | Menu Title Text Length | M GSM 03.38 Default - "Input" Max Length = 16: 4 to 19 | Menu Title Text | M GSM 11.11 / 1 - "Input" Max Length = 7 4 | Encoding Alpha Identifier(0x80) | M 5 to 19 | Menu Title Text padded with 0x00 | M GSM 11.11 / 2 - "Input" Max Length = 13 4 | Encoding Alpha Identifier(0x81) | M 5 | Menu Title Text Length | M 6 | 0xFF | M 7 to 19 | Menu Title Text | M GSM 11.11 / 2 - "Input" Max Length = 12 4 | Encoding Alpha Identifier(0x82) | M 5 | Menu Title Text Length | M 6 | 0xFF | M 7 | 0xFF | M 8 to 19 | Menu Title Text | M Unused bytes are set to 0xFF.
Encoding: SMS Default 7 - bit Alphabet
Based On: G + D SIM Guideline Wib 1.3 equipped(U) SIM cards G + D AUR Specification WIB Java Client

data.name: inputTextBox.HelpString
data.value:
Input - 1 to 16 Characters:
This field will will be used to generate date in the following EF attributes: EF SUME - Menu Title Text EF Menu Title - Menu Title Text EF SPN - Service Provider Name EF PNN - Network Full Name
Based on: G + D SIM Guideline Wib 1.3 equipped(U) SIM cards ETSI TS 131.102 ETSI TS 102.222

data.name: SUMETextBox.HelpString
data.value:
EF SUME(SetUpMenu Elements) - 30 Bytes:
Bytes | Description | M / O 1 | Alpha Identifier Tag(0x05) | M 2 | Menu Title Length | M 3 to X | Menu Title Text Attribute | O X + 1 | Icon Idenfier Tag(0x1E) | O X + 2 | Length(0x02) | O X + 3 | Icon Qualifier | O X + 4 | Icon Identifier | O Unused bytes are set to 0xFF.
Encoding: SMS Default 7 - bit Alphabet
Based On: ETSI TS 131.102 ETSI TS 102.222 ETSI TS 102.223

data.name: PSKTabPage.HelpString
KCVTabPage.HelpString
data.value:
Based on GPC_SPE_034, GlobalPlatform Card Specification 2.3.1 , GlobalPlatform, March 2018, Section B5 Remote Provisioning Architecture for Embedded UICC 3.1, GSMA, May 2016, Annex F
How KCV (Key Checksum Value) is calculated:
Insert "Key"(Size depends on the Crypto Algorithm); Click in "Calculate" button.
block (16 Characters - 8 bytes) = 0000000000000000;
KCV (6 Characters - 3 bytes) = First 3 bytes of encrypted "block" with the chosen Crypto Algorithm ECB NO_PADDING using "Key" as a key.
